{"word":"ἀρνέομαι","slug":"ἀρνέομαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀρνέομαι</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:derived, derivation'>Deriv.</a> uncertain\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><a href='S:Deponent Verb, i.e. a Verb of Middle or Passive form with Active sense'>Dep.</a> <a href='S:opposed to'>opp. to</a> <el>φημί</el>, <i>to deny, disown</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:opposed to'>opp. to</a> <el>δίδωμι</el>, <i>to decline to give, refuse</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b>absol <i>to say no, decline, refuse</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>4. </b>dependent clauses are put in <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, with or without <el>μή</el>, <i>to deny that</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, attic <p/></div>"}]}